==English==
=== Etymology ===
From Old Dutch ''holt lant'' ("wood land"). A popular but [[false etymology]] holds that it is derived from ''hol land'' ("hollow land"), inspired by the [[lowland|low-lying]] [[geography]] of both the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] and the English region ([[Wikipedia:Holland, Lincolnshire|Holland, Lincolnshire]]).

===Proper noun===
'''Holland'''

# [[The Netherlands]].
# a region of [[The Netherlands]].

